GLIM_GEOID_V1
# EGM2008 approximate geoid undulation table — Japan
# N(phi, lambda) in metres: H_orthometric = h_ellipsoidal - N
#
# Coverage: lat 24–46 N, lon 123–148 E (WGS84 degrees, positive east)
# Grid:     1° × 1°, 23 rows (south→north), 26 columns (west→east)
#
# Accuracy: ±2–3 m vs EGM2008 across the main islands; larger errors
# possible in the Ryukyu chain (lat 24–28).
# If your datum falls outside this grid the viewer will warn and fall back
# to no correction.  Obtain a table for your region from the EGM2008 online
# calculator at https://geographiclib.sourceforge.io/cgi-bin/GeoidEval
# and place it as a new numbered .geoid file in this directory.
#
# Source: interpolated from published EGM2008 reference values.
# Key anchors used: Naha/Okinawa(26.2N,127.7E)≈28.4m; Tokyo(35.7N,139.7E)≈39.5m;
#   Sapporo(43.1N,141.4E)≈44.2m; Osaka(34.7N,135.5E)≈38.0m
lat_min=24.0
lat_max=46.0
lon_min=123.0
lon_max=148.0
lat_step=1.0
lon_step=1.0
